This purpose continues to drive us forward, supported by a culture deeply rooted in rigorous fundamental research, a relentless pursuit of investment insights, and a commitment to continuous innovation on behalf of our clients. At Ranieri Asset Management, we value the free exchange of ideas throughout our organization, fostering an environment where diverse perspectives thrive. As a private and independent investment manager, Ranieri Asset Management stands apart from the majority of large asset management firms. Unlike those tied to public ownership or other financial institutions, our 100% independent ownership and exclusive focus on our clients' needs enable us to align ourselves fully with their long-term interests. With no external parent or public shareholders to answer to, we have the freedom to operate with an enduring client-centric perspective. By exclusively dedicating ourselves to investment management and avoiding proprietary trading or market-making operations, we concentrate all our efforts on our core expertise. This concentrated focus allows us to deliver the highest level of service and dedication to our clients. Moreover, our employees and their families have a personal stake in our clients' success, with significant personal capital invested alongside our clients' assets. Additionally, 100% of employee deferred cash compensation is directly linked to the performance of our team and firm strategies, demonstrating our shared commitment to achieving exceptional outcomes together. At Ranieri Asset Management, we are driven by the belief that our independence, client-centric focus, and alignment of interests create an environment conducive to long-term success. We are dedicated to delivering superior investment management solutions while building lasting relationships with our clients based on trust, transparency, and shared prosperity.

They house one of the most compelling collections of contemporary art in the world, comprising roughly 7000 objects, and have a diverse history of ground-breaking, historically-significant exhibitions. They are committed to the collection, presentation, and interpretation of art created after 1940, in all media, and to preserving that work for future generations. They provide leadership in the field by identifying and presenting the most significant and challenging art of their time, actively supporting the creation of new work, and producing original scholarship. With three distinct venues in Los Angeles—MOCA Grand Avenue, The Geffen Contemporary at MOCA, and MOCA Pacific Design Center—and Michael Heizer’s seminal artwork Double Negative (1969-70) in the Nevada desert, they engage audiences through an ambitious program of exhibitions, educational programs, and publishing.

Description: OpenPlacement brings transparency and real-time vacancy information to care transitions.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: OpenPlacement brings transparency and real-time vacancy information to care transitions. Today, when a patient is discharged from a hospital or skilled nursing facility to post-acute care such as assisted living, homecare, board and care, RCFE (to just name a few) or needs rehab care, durable medical equipment (DME) or even transportation services, the discharge planner, patient, caretaker and family rely on antiquated materials and hours of phone calls to locate the provider which fits their exact needs. OpenPlacement  web application serves patients and their caregivers by helping them search and qualify care providers that best meet their specific needs. OpenPlacement then connects the patient, caretaker, family and/or care professional directly with the care provider. OpenPlacement gives care providers direct access to new referral sources at hospitals and with patients who otherwise would never know about them leading to increased business and streamlining the process of patient intake. OpenPlacement founding team has a combined 25+ years of experience in healthcare and firsthand saw today challenges and inefficiencies of care transition. The company was part of Rock Health's 4th incubator class. Please learn more at www.OpenPlacement.com.
